This paper deals with game theory and optimization, which are core topics in computer science. The paper's focus on multi-objective games suggests that it could be categorized under cs.GT (Game Theory) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a polynomial-time algorithm suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper's emphasis on evaluating actions based on multiple objectives suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
